SIMPLE: washy
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Washy
<hw>Wash"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Wash</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Watery; damp; soft.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Washy</xex> ooze.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Lacking substance or strength; weak; thin; dilute;
feeble; <as>as, <ex>washy</ex> tea; <ex>washy</ex>
resolutions</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q> A polish . . . not over thin and <qex>washy</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir H. Wotton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Not firm or hardy; liable to sweat profusely with
labor; <as>as, a <ex>washy</ex> horse</as>.</def> <mark>[Local, U.
S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wasite</ent>⟦br⟧
